quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  37,91,"Then he turned to their âlihah (gods) and said: "
  37,92,""
  37,93,"Then he turned upon them, striking (them) with (his) right hand."
  38,70,""
  38,71,"(Remember) when your Lord said to the angels: "
  38,72,"So when I have fashioned him and breathed into him (his) soul created by Me, then you fall down prostrate to him."
  39,55,""
  39,56,"Lest a person should say: "
  39,57,"Or (lest) he should say: "
  40,34,"And indeed Yûsuf (Joseph) did come to you, in times gone by, with clear signs, but you ceased not to doubt in that which he did bring to you: till when he died you said: "
  40,35,"Those who dispute about the Ayât (proofs, evidence, verses, lessons, signs, revelations, etc.) of Allâh, without any authority that has come to them, it is greatly hateful and disgusting to Allâh and to those who believe. Thus does Allâh seal up the heart of every arrogant, tyrant. (So they cannot guide themselves to the Right Path)."
  40,36,"And Fir‘aun (Pharaoh) said: "
  41,13,"But if they turn away, then say (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم): "
  41,14,"When the Messengers came to them, from before them and behind them (saying): "
  41,15,"As for ‘Âd, they were arrogant in the land without right, and they said: "